observationText: The WT ES cell line was used as a control in experiments comparing gene expression and differentiation potential with other embryonic stem cell lines.
The WT ES cell line exhibited normal pluripotency and self-renewal capabilities typical of embryonic stem cells.
The WT ES cell line exhibited normal karyotype stability over multiple passages in culture.
Gene expression analysis showed the WT ES cell line clustered closely with other pluripotent embryonic stem cell lines.
